The <definition> of the "Name" field is the full name of the individual. The <intent> is to identify the person associated with the record. The <data_type> is a string. There are no specific <constraints> or <validation_rules> beyond standard name formatting. An <example> value is "Sky Person". The <is_required> field is true, as names are essential for identification. The <business_context> involves personal identification in business records.

The <definition> of the "Position" field is the job title or role of the individual. The <intent> is to specify the person's role within the organization. The <data_type> is a string. There are no specific <constraints> or <validation_rules> beyond standard title formatting. An <example> value is "Head Counsel -". The <is_required> field is true, as roles are crucial for organizational structure. The <business_context> involves defining responsibilities and hierarchy.

The <definition> of the "Date" field is the specific date associated with the record. The <intent> is to provide a timestamp for the event or record. The <units> are in date format. The <data_type> is a date. The <constraints> include valid date formats. An <example> value is "20 July 2020". The <format> is "DD Month YYYY". The <validation_rules> require adherence to the specified date format. The <is_required> field is true, as dates are essential for chronological tracking. The <business_context> involves time-based record-keeping and event tracking.
